	<text>
		<body>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName> <date>20 April 1830 1850 &#40;&#63;&#41;</date></p>
				<p>My dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">So favorable an opportunity as this cannot escape me to say<lb/> a few words to you after the lapse of time intervened.  The state of our<lb/> uncle&#39;s health is exceedingly delicate&#44; his limbs will scarcely bear him<lb/> along.  So debilitated is he by the wretched cough attendant on his asthma.<lb/>  Rest has he none by day or night&#44; and altho he has had strength enough<lb/> to crawl to my office I really think he will not get home without extreme<lb/> fatigue.  I do not mention these facts with a view of inducing you to<lb/> come or should it interfere in your arrangements.  But I am certain a<lb/> few days of your company with uncle would so gratify him that the experi&#45;<lb/>ment is worth trying.  Could you not be spared a few days next week&#63;  I<lb/> am not so sure that I am not taking upon myself a responsibility in<lb/> these remarks that might induce you to come on at all hazards.  Our<lb/> friend <persName>Mr. Etting</persName> will tell you how debilitated and feeble uncle looks&#44;<lb/> and I am only giving you my own impression what I think would delight him.<lb/>  Contrary to &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; the least idea that I have made this communi&#45;<lb/>cation.  Hence <hi rend="underline">should</hi> you come&#44; say that you heard that uncle was sick<lb/> and having a few days leisure you came over to see him.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Mama has been confined to her bed &#38; room for some weeks tho<lb/> so far recovered as to speak of coming down <add>Hebrew</add> God willing.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">A letter from <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> yesterday.  All well &#38; things is<lb/> status quo.<lb/>  Happiness attend you.<lb/>  Yours&#44;</p>
				<p><hi rend="underline"><persName role="author">D. Judah</persName></hi></p>
				<p><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p>Addressed<lb/> <sic><addressee>Rev Isaac Leezer</addressee></sic><lb/> attention<lb/> <persName>Mrs Etting</persName></p>
		</body>
